title.$t: Support our short film, THE SHATTERED MIND via Kickstarter

media$title.$t: Support our short film, THE SHATTERED MIND via Kickstarter

media$description.$t:
http://kck.st/10Cd1h3   KICKSTARTER FUNDRAISING GOAL $7,000

The film is centered upon a proud Black Deaf family with a captivating story that has never been told before in the mainstream film industry. It will star deaf and hearing actors, Rosavetta Jackson, Jubil Khan, Reb Grant, Curtis Babers and Antilla Zulkifl. "THE SHATTERED MIND" is a 30-minute short film that explores a black deaf family's journey while their daughter, Zhane Rain, to be played by Rosavetta Jackson, struggles to overcome adversity; traumatic childhood past and hearing loss.

title.$t: Part 1 - Secrets in a Black Deaf Family - Feature Film Support

media$title.$t: Part 1 - Secrets in a Black Deaf Family - Feature Film Support

media$description.$t:
Support our film project.DONATION LINK --- http://www.indiegogo.com/zhanerain

Zhane Rain is an intense and carefree high school senior with three generations of both hearing and Deaf family members who unravels family secrets behind the traumatic brain injury that caused her deafness. 

This thought-provoking psychodrama explores family relationships, teen issues and coping with adversity. Its messages resonate with a much broader audience, and families of any make-up can relate to issues they face in their lives. It also promotes social consciousness and raises awareness of deaf culture within an African-American Culture and society's tolerance of difference.

title.$t: INFORMATION ACCESS IS CRITICAL. A BLIND MAN GETS KILLED BY MTA SUBWAY.

media$title.$t: INFORMATION ACCESS IS CRITICAL. A BLIND MAN GETS KILLED BY MTA SUBWAY.

media$description.$t:
Order your DVD copy at http://jadefilm.com to see the complete film. You are watching a clip excerpt from a documentary, 9/11 FEAR IN SILENCE: THE FORGOTTEN UNDERDOGS.

This documentary film was produced in 2006 by a Deaf filmmaker, Jade and was nominated for best produced documentary. 

THE 2ND PART OF THE COMPLETE DVD: Disclose issues and concerns about our quest for resolutions to the City and Government to improve equal access within the NYC MTA transit system that failed to meet the needs of the Deaf and Hard of Hearing commuters, evacuation designed safe areas under the subway stations for both the Deaf and Hard of Hearing people, the Deaf-Blind and people with disabilities, 9-1-1 accessible emergency procedures, emergency preparedness for immediate evacuation, information on alert systems, accessible emergency communication and notification within the law enforcement, hospitals, and fire department -- all within the city, state and federal operating system. The list goes on. "When information is 'not accessible' for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing people, then ignorance kills, silence kills, fear kills, and neglect kills. INFORMATION IS POWER," quoted Jade.

title.$t: 9/11 - 10 YEARS LATER  - ARE THEY READY FOR DEAF PEOPLE?

media$title.$t: 9/11 - 10 YEARS LATER  - ARE THEY READY FOR DEAF PEOPLE?

media$description.$t:
Order your DVD copy at http://jadefilm.com to see the complete film.  EXCERPT FROM DOCUMENTARY (PART 2) "9/11 FEAR IN SILENCE"

9/11 was covered from every perspective except ours, the deaf survivors. Best Produced Documentary by Ann Marie "Jade" Bryan. 

The second part of the film disclose issues and concerns about our quest for resolutions to the City and Government to improve equal access within the NYC MTA transit system that failed to meet the needs of the Deaf and Hard of Hearing commuters, evacuation designed safe areas under the subway stations for both the Deaf and Hard of Hearing people, the Deaf-Blind and people with disabilities, 9-1-1 accessible emergency procedures, emergency preparedness for immediate evacuation, information on alert systems, accessible emergency communication and notification within the law enforcement, hospitals, and fire department -- all within the city, state and federal operating system. The list goes on. "When information is 'not accessible' for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing people, then ignorance kills, silence kills, fear kills, and neglect kills. INFORMATION IS POWER," quoted Jade.
